article.description: Jonathan Williams scored 21 points and Nate Navigato added 20 as Toledo rebounded from back-to-back losses for the first time this season and routed Bethune-Cookman 102-68 Saturday.
article.headline: Toledo dismantles Bethune-Cookman 102-68
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio -- Jonathan Williams scored 21 points and Nate Navigato added 20 as Toledo rebounded from back-to-back losses for the first time this season and routed Bethune-Cookman 102-68 Saturday. Toledo (7-4) was coming off defeats against Detroit and Oakland on Dec. 9 and 12. Against Bethune-Cookman (4-7), Zach Garber scored 17 points, Jaelan Sanford had 16 and Stuckey Mosley finished with 10. Toledo shot 54.8 percent from the field and 46.2 percent from beyond the 3-point arc. Diamante Lewis' dunk with 9:13 to play before the half cut Toledo's lead to 22-17, but the Rockets outscored the Wildcats 29-16 to take a 51-33 halftime lead. Early in the second half, Williams scored on a layup and hit two-of-three free throws after a technical foul against Bethune-Cookman to make it 70-39 with 15:20 to play. Randy Holmes led the Wildcats with 16 points, Jordan Potts had 15 and LaRon Smith chipped in 10.
